HEADWORD: Pillau
<hw>Pil*lau"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Per. & Turk.
<ets>pilau</ets>.]</ety> <def>An Oriental dish consisting of rice boiled
with mutton, fat, or butter.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>pilau</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

